  "response": "Yes, that's correct. Money laundering is illegal in virtually every country around the world. It involves the process of making large amounts of money generated by criminal activity, such as drug trafficking or terrorist funding, appear to be legally obtained. This is typically done by disguising the true origin of the money through a series of complex transactions and transfers.\n\nGovernments and financial institutions have established rigorous laws and regulations to detect and prevent money laundering. These include requirements for financial institutions to maintain certain records, report large or suspicious transactions, and verify the identities of their clients. Violations of these laws can result in severe penalties, including large fines and imprisonment for individuals and entities involved.",
